Here's how to handle each scenario in MSTest:

## 1. Windows-only (Registry)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void TestRegistryLookup()
{
    if (!OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
    {
        Assert.Inconclusive("Requires Windows registry.");
    }

    // Registry test code...
}
```

Or create a reusable custom attribute (MSTest v3+):

```csharp
[AttributeUsage(AttributeTargets.Method)]
public class WindowsOnlyTestMethodAttribute : TestMethodAttribute
{
    public override TestResult[] Execute(ITestMethod testMethod)
    {
        if (!OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
            return new[] { new TestResult { Outcome = UnitTestOutcome.Inconclusive,
                TestFailureException = new AssertInconclusiveException("Windows only") } };
        return base.Execute(testMethod);
    }
}

[WindowsOnlyTestMethod]
public void TestRegistryLookup() { /* ... */ }
```

## 2. Skip in CI (requires GPU)

Use `[TestCategory]` and filter at the runner level:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("RequiresGPU")]
public void TestGpuRendering() { /* ... */ }
```

In CI, exclude with: `dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=RequiresGPU"`

Or check an environment variable at runtime:

```csharp
if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") == "true")
    Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI — requires local GPU.");
```

## 3. Flaky external API — Retry

MSTest v3.2+ has a built-in `[Retry]` attribute:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)] // retries up to 3 times on failure
[Timeout(10000)]
public void TestWeatherApi() { /* ... */ }
```

## 4. Cleanup on failure — `[TestCleanup]`

`[TestCleanup]` runs **regardless** of test outcome:

```csharp
[TestClass]
public class TempFileTests
{
    private string _tempFile = null!;

    [TestInitialize]
    public void Setup()
    {
        _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void TestWriteAndRead()
    {
        File.WriteAllText(_tempFile, "data");
        Assert.AreEqual("data", File.ReadAllText(_tempFile));
    }

    [TestCleanup]
    public void Cleanup()
    {
        if (File.Exists(_tempFile))
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
    }
}
```

---

**Summary of patterns:**

| Scenario | Approach |
|----------|----------|
| OS-specific | `Assert.Inconclusive()` or custom `TestMethodAttribute` |
| CI skip | `[TestCategory]` + `--filter` exclusion |
| Flaky/retry | `[Retry(N)]` (MSTest v3.2+) |
| Guaranteed cleanup | `[TestCleanup]` method |
